        "created_at": "2025-12-28T15:51:46.166Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Here are some ideas to curb the problem of lack of moderation in groups with the aim of transforming abuse from free to expensive:</p>\n<p>Phase 0 ‚Äì new member (days 0‚Äì7)</p>\n<p>ephemeral messages 12h<br>\nno media<br>\nno links<br>\nstrict rate limit (e.g., 1 message / 1 hour)<br>\nObjective: if someone wants to cause serious damage, they have neither the time nor the space to do so.</p>\n<p>Phase 1 ‚Äì ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre doing well‚Äù (7‚Äì30 days)</p>\n<p>ephemeral 1 week<br>\nmedia allowed but no forwarding<br>\nlinks allowed but preview disabled<br>\nObjective: reduce spam, phishing, and shitty links.</p>\n<p>Phase 2 ‚Äì Stable member (30‚Äì90 days)</p>\n<p>ephemeral 2 weeks<br>\nmedia ok<br>\nlinks ok<br>\nnormal rate limit</p>\n<p>Phase 3 ‚Äì ‚ÄúTrusted‚Äù member</p>\n<p>full participation<br>\nThis trust scale is: simple, understandable, non-arbitrary, and above all, automatable.</p>\n<p>Other thoughts: messages from new members are not immediately visible to everyone (as is currently the case with spoiler formatting or appropriate alert messages).</p>\n<p>For the first X days: immediately visible only to admins and others with a delay (e.g., 5‚Äì10 min to block porn/doxxing before it explodes and to nip serial trolls in the bud</p>\n<p>Shadow ban (local shadow ban)<br>\nPast messages from the banned user are automatically hidden, displaying a placeholder such as: ‚ÄúMessages removed by admin for violation of rules‚Äù</p>\n<p>Your thoughts?</p>",
