        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/rassilon1963/{size}/31625_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-12T12:49:39.307Z",
        "cooked": "<p>those sound to me very much like social-oriented features, for platforms where you talk to people you don‚Äôt know and don‚Äôt trust, like a forum. not really the vibe of a Signal group.<br>\ni am personally very much in favour of the <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/ability-for-group-admins-to-delete-any-message-for-everyone/22229\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Ability for group admins to delete any message for everyone</a>, since you already need to trust group admins and that feature has many uses, not only with public or semi-public forum-as-a-group. i agree this should also be extended to when a member is removed from a group, with the option to delete all of their messages with a single click.<br>\nbut anything beyond that sounds to me like an attempt to turn Signal into a forum, which to me, is out of scope. see also this thread: <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/add-social-features-social-timeline/11528\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Add Social Features / Social Timeline</a></p>",
